本列表收錄'''歷史上的LGBT人物'''及其相關歷史事件。很多[[文明|文明]]或[[社會|社會]]都存在過同性別之間的[[親密關係|親密關係]]（包括[[變裝|變裝]]在內）<ref>{{cite web|title=Ford and Beach's "Homosexual Behavior," 1951|url=http://outhistory.org/exhibits/show/native-americans-gay-americans/1900s/ford-and-beach|quote=The authors collected information on homosexuality in seventy-six societies and found that male homosexual activities were regarded favorably in forty-nine (sixty-four percent).|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002180540/http://outhistory.org/exhibits/show/native-americans-gay-americans/1900s/ford-and-beach|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Carrier, J.M.|title=Homosexual behavior in cross-cultural perspective|date=1985|url=https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/fd1b/a5f28868330815064734ce08b53162493960.pdf|quote=There is some evidence in support of this linking of gender role and homosexual behavior in societies making an accommodation and providing a social role for cross-gender behaving individuals.|accessdate=2019-04-18|archive-date=2019-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190309022219/http://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/fd1b/a5f28868330815064734ce08b53162493960.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而就[[靈長目|靈長目]]動物和當代[[原始社會|原始社會]]存在同性[[親密關係|親密關係]]的事實來看，可以推測從[[舊石器時代|舊石器時代]]和[[新石器時代|新石器時代]]起，同性發生[[性關係|性關係]]的現象就存在了<ref>{{cite journal |author1=张杰 |title=同性恋的早期状态与自然观念的演变 |journal=中国性科学 |date=2011 |url=http://www.zgxkx.org/xingkexue/xingwenhua/201104/523.html |author= |access-date=2019-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228065819/http://www.zgxkx.org/xingkexue/xingwenhua/201104/523.html |archive-date=2019-02-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=James Neill|title=The Origins and Role of Same-Sex Relations in Human Societies|date=2008|isbn=9780786452477|page=82|url=https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=1ha9GgWNmy0C&lpg=PA82&ots=MLJys4nVIk&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA82#v=onepage&q&f=false|access-date=2015-10-03|archive-date=2019-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228065958/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=1ha9GgWNmy0C&lpg=PA82&ots=MLJys4nVIk&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA82#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有[[考古學|考古學]]家對[[西西里島|西西里島]]安達拉石洞（{{tsl|en|Grotta dell'Addaura|Grotta dell'Addaura}}）遺址雕刻圖案作出的其中一種解釋，是認為當中一幅場景是在描繪兩名男性間的性愛活動<ref>{{cite web|title=Queer heritage: a timeline|url=http://www.aaronsgayinfo.com/timeline/FtimeBC.html|accessdate=2012-11-02|archive-date=2020-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218141118/http://www.aaronsgayinfo.com/timeline/FtimeBC.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

歷史人物是否为[[同性戀|同性戀]]或[[雙性戀|雙性戀]]，時常會是人們爭辯的話題。然而關於这方面的確切資訊卻很少，人们只能利用有限的证据来推斷或[[詮釋學|詮釋]]。列表人物的列名，是以親密情感或性關係來推測，從現代的標準來看不一定會被认为是同性恋或雙性戀<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|author=吳瑞元|title=古代中國同性情慾歷史的研究回顧與幾個觀點的批評|year=2000|publisher=麥田|pages=158-197|url=http://sex.ncu.edu.tw/publication_cn/2000/jo7/pdf/11.pdf|quote=由此來看，能夠列入與強調的同性戀相關人物只是著重於有否「同性情慾關係」而已。拋開現代對「同性戀者」的醫學界定，這樣來檢視在（範例三）矛鋒所稱的「同性戀者」或者是其他書中的「同性戀關係」，其實都是指有「同性情慾關連」的人，無關乎歷史人物的情慾強度、意願、身份認同或者是異性性史|access-date=2016-03-05|archive-date=2015-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150419220920/http://sex.ncu.edu.tw/publication_cn/2000/jo7/pdf/11.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。親密情感可能是[[浪漫友情|浪漫友情]]的展現，未必涉有[[情慾|情慾]]關係<ref>{{cite web|author1=Heather Elizabeth Peterson|title=The Misguided Search for 'Homoeroticism'|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111017090047/http://www.gay-art-history.org/gay-history/gay-literature/homosexuality-debate/history-homosexuality-friendship-sexual-love/history-homosexuality-friendship-sexual-love.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Brett & Kate McKay|title=The History and Nature of Man Friendships|url=http://www.artofmanliness.com/2008/08/24/the-history-and-nature-of-man-friendships/|accessdate=2016-03-05|archive-date=2018-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412022934/https://www.artofmanliness.com/2008/08/24/the-history-and-nature-of-man-friendships/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。性關係的發生不必然表徵[[性傾向|性傾向]]和情慾品質，而可能是迫於生計的[[賣淫|賣淫]]，迎合社會形象成家生子，或[[士人|士人]]表現灑脫風流的一時享受。經驗過同性或異性性行為的歷史人物，並不能確定該個體符合現代觀點下「同性戀」、「雙性戀」的[[身份認同|身份認同]]<ref>{{cite journal|author1=吳瑞元|title=在情慾的視野中發現同性情慾歷史——情慾歷史的特色與古代同性情慾歷史的建構|journal=史匯|date=1997|volume=2|pages=81-102|url=http://asp.fhjh.ntpc.edu.tw/t98fh05/profile/profile_data/articles/9700NCU_journal_discover_same_sex_history.pdf|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305232918/http://asp.fhjh.ntpc.edu.tw/t98fh05/profile/profile_data/articles/9700NCU_journal_discover_same_sex_history.pdf|archivedate=2016-03-05|access-date=2016-03-05}}</ref>。

不過由於過往歷史對[[LGBT|LGBT]]{{tsl|en|Consciousness raising|認同意識}}的形成有所影響，同性情慾和親密友誼，仍是[[LGBT歷史|LGBT歷史]]的重要面向<ref>{{cite web|author1=Paul Halsall|title=People with A History: Introduction|url=http://legacy.fordham.edu/halsall/pwh/pwh-intro.asp|quote=The history of sexuality, and especially homosexual activity, is a subject for LGB history...There is thus some reason to claim the history of friendship is of special interest to modern LGBs, who preserve with their subcultures a tradition of intense emotional same-sex friendship, both with sexual partners and with others.|access-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308195655/http://legacy.fordham.edu/halsall/pwh/pwh-intro.asp|archive-date=2016-03-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

